---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Resources"
  description="Comprehensive resources on frontier AI risk, treaty pathways, policy engagement, and movement organizing."
>
  <section class="section-root">
    <div class="container-root">
      <h1>AI Safety Resource Hub</h1>
      <p>
        A comprehensive guide for students, journalists, policymakers, researchers, and civil society leaders who want
        to understand frontier AI risk and support practical governance action.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-root section-root-accent">
    <div class="container-root">
      <h2>Start Here: Core PauseAI Materials</h2>
      <div class="resources-grid">
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>PauseAI Nigeria Theory of Change</h3>
          <p>Complete chapter strategy: mission, outcomes, assumptions, and the full change pathway for Nigeria.</p>
          <a href="/blog/pauseai-nigeria-theory-of-change/">Read full chapter theory of change</a>
        </article>
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>Global Proposal</h3>
          <p>The core call: halt frontier AI development until systems are safe and democratically controlled.</p>
          <a href="https://pauseai.info/proposal" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Read proposal</a>
        </article>
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>Theory of Change</h3>
          <p>How movement growth, lobbying, protests, and public communication create conditions for an international pause.</p>
          <a href="https://pauseai.info/theory-of-change" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Read theory of change</a>
        </article>
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>How You Can Help</h3>
          <p>Action pathways for citizens: organize, communicate, lobby, and support local chapters.</p>
          <a href="https://pauseai.info/action" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">View action guide</a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-root">
    <div class="container-root">
      <h2>Understanding the AI Risk Landscape</h2>
      <div class="resources-grid">
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>Risk Overview</h3>
          <p>High-level map of catastrophic, systemic, and governance risks from frontier AI.</p>
          <a href="https://pauseai.info/risks" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Open risks overview</a>
        </article>
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>Urgency and Pace</h3>
          <p>Why AI progress speed changes policy timelines and reduces room for reactive governance.</p>
          <a href="https://pauseai.info/urgency" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Read urgency brief</a>
        </article>
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>Dangerous Capabilities</h3>
          <p>Technical and operational capabilities that make uncontrolled frontier systems high risk.</p>
          <a href="https://pauseai.info/dangerous-capabilities" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Explore capabilities</a>
        </article>
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>Psychology of X-Risk</h3>
          <p>Why societies and institutions often underreact to slow-building existential threats.</p>
          <a href="https://pauseai.info/psychology-of-x-risk" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Read psychology explainer</a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-root section-root-accent">
    <div class="container-root">
      <h2>Policy and Treaty Pathways</h2>
      <p>
        The most realistic routes to a pause are international treaty processes and coordinated supply-chain controls.
      </p>
      <div class="resources-grid">
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>How a Treaty Could Work</h3>
          <p>PauseAI US treaty framing: pause provisions, agency design, verification, and enforcement.</p>
          <a href="https://www.pauseai-us.org/howtreaty/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Read treaty explainer</a>
        </article>
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>Policy FAQ</h3>
          <p>Answers to common objections: "What about China?" "Are you against all AI?" and enforcement concerns.</p>
          <a href="https://www.pauseai-us.org/policyfaq/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Open policy FAQ</a>
        </article>
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>Educational Crisis Brief</h3>
          <p>A structured deep dive on control risk, warning signs, near-term trajectories, and governance choices.</p>
          <a href="https://www.pauseai-us.org/resources/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">View educational resources</a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-root">
    <div class="container-root">
      <h2>Expert Statements and Evidence</h2>
      <div class="resources-grid">
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>Statement on AI Risk (2023)</h3>
          <p>Foundational statement calling AI extinction risk a global priority alongside nuclear war and pandemics.</p>
          <a href="https://www.safe.ai/statement-on-ai-risk" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Read statement</a>
        </article>
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>Superintelligence Statement</h3>
          <p>Large-scale public and expert support for prohibiting superintelligence before it is provably controllable.</p>
          <a href="https://superintelligence-statement.org/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">View statement</a>
        </article>
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>Polls and Surveys</h3>
          <p>Public-attitude and expert-opinion data relevant to slowing AI development and governance support.</p>
          <a href="https://pauseai.info/polls-and-surveys" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">See polls</a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-root section-root-accent">
    <div class="container-root">
      <h2>Nigerian Institutions and Context</h2>
      <p>
        These links are useful for grounding global AI governance conversations in Nigerian regulatory and policy institutions.
      </p>
      <div class="resources-grid">
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>NITDA</h3>
          <p>National digital policy and technology regulation touchpoint.</p>
          <a href="https://nitda.gov.ng" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Visit NITDA</a>
        </article>
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>NCC</h3>
          <p>Communications and digital infrastructure regulator relevant to AI deployment impacts.</p>
          <a href="https://ncc.gov.ng" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Visit NCC</a>
        </article>
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>National Assembly</h3>
          <p>Legislative entry point for hearings, briefings, and AI safety policy proposals.</p>
          <a href="https://nass.gov.ng" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Visit National Assembly</a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-root">
    <div class="container-root">
      <h2>For Organizers and Volunteers</h2>
      <div class="resources-grid">
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>Email Builder</h3>
          <p>Templates and tools for direct outreach to public officials.</p>
          <a href="https://pauseai.info/email-builder" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Open email builder</a>
        </article>
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>Lobby Tips</h3>
          <p>Practical tactics for effective and responsible policy engagement.</p>
          <a href="https://pauseai.info/lobby-tips" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Read lobby tips</a>
        </article>
        <article class="card-root card-pad">
          <h3>Communities</h3>
          <p>Join local and global PauseAI communities to coordinate action.</p>
          <a href="https://pauseai.info/communities" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Find communities</a>
        </article>
      </div>
      <p class="resources-note">
        Note: This resource hub is a living page. We will continue adding Nigeria-specific legal briefs, media kits,
        university debate packs, and downloadable policymaker one-pagers.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .resources-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-2);
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
  }
  .card-pad {
    padding: var(--space-2);
  }
  .card-pad h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  .resources-note {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
</style>
